  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In the present study, the primary aim was to evaluate if oxycodone-naloxone combination
      compared to oxycodone reduced opioid induced constipation in patients with or without chronic
      opioid treatment undergoing spine surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
